Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[The east coast of the US has received a large amount of rain this
year (2009) and has had a relatively cool summer. These are ideal
conditions for the mosquito to propagate. The disease has been found
as far north as Canada and Maine. It is sad, then, that owners would
be caught unaware and forego a lifesaving vaccine!

While humans can catch the disease, it can be caught from the
mosquito not from infected horses. - Mod.TG]
